Tweaks version 2.1.0.
Fix a few warnings from newer compilers.

Only compile UIAlertView code with a deployment target below iOS 8.

UIAlertView was deprecated in iOS 9. If code is not targeting iOS 7,
then there is no need in compiling it in, and it prevents a warning.

This is in addition to compiling it out in app extensions, where it
is never allowed.

Moved FBTweakAction block execution from _FBTweakTableViewCell's setSelected: to _FBTweakCollectionViewController's didSelectRowAtIndexPath:. setSelected: is a poor choice as it's intended for UI updates, and UITableView calls setSelected: multiple times. This fixes the bug where FBTweakActions are executed twice. (#110)

Baseline code assumes that the DATA segment immediately follows the TEXT segment so that file offsets can be used to compute in memory addresses. The modified code eliminates this assumption and access the FBTweak section correctly when there are holes in the virtual address space.

Baseline code assumes that the DATA segment immediately follows the TEXT segment so that file offsets can be used to compute in memory addresses. The modified code eliminates this assumption and access the FBTweak section correctly when there are holes in the virtual address space.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/facebook/Tweaks

Conflicts:
	FBTweak/_FBTweakTableViewCell.m
	FBTweakExample/FBAppDelegate.m
Added Facebook licence to the _FBSliderView.m file.
Code refactored, implemented color selection controller , resolved project warnings, changed demo project to edit background color.
Implemented color selection controller. Refactored RGB & HSB color views.
Refactored rgba color components selection view.

Added in full export support.

 - offloaded the dictionary representation to FBTweakStore
 - adjusted toolbar to not have a hardcoded height
 - Cleaned up tableview insets, and cleaned up mail handling
 - Fixed plist exporting

Support constant values in tweaks.

Two fixes here:
 - Cast points to (void *) before storing in struct to avoid warning.
 - Update _Generic to support const types in addition to regular ones.
Link to explanation for compilation issues with custom Cocoapods configurations.
Changed keyboard manager to make it reusable all over the project.
Implemented keyboard manager

Fix bug making it impossible to change tweak values.

The block superclass loop was running one too many times, so it treated all NSObject subclasses as blocks.

Sort tweak categories and collections by name.

This results in a more consistent ordering, making it easier to find the tweaks you're looking for.

Add support for Action tweaks.

Rather than storing a value, action tweaks run a (global) block on activation. They're useful for things like checking for updates, testing crash reporting (if you make one that crashes on tap), or launching custom debug UIs.

This adds support for action tweaks and basic tests to ensure the macros compile and work more than once in the same scope.

Adjust macro definitions to cast minimum and maximum values to the same type as the default.

This fixes strange values observed when they were of different (yet compatible) types, often float and double. Update unit tests to test the corrected behavior, confirm tests pass after the change.

Nicer stepper values when adjusting tweaks.

 - Don't write the value back to the stepper when it just came from it. This fixes press-and-hold.
 - Use ceil(abs(log10(x))) to determine the displayed precision. This makes sure that each stepper press changes the text display.
 - Limit stepper adjustments to 1.0. For large values (like font sizes), this makes sure you can always pick each point value.
Adjust code formatting for alert view.
